Please see README.original for original ustr README file.
---------------------------------------------------------

To cross-compile for an ARM architecture:

Compilation process needs inbuild 

autoconf_64b and autoconf_vsnprintf executables,
so first compile them according to your host machine.

Then, in:

ustr-import
ustr-conf.h
ustr-conf-debug.h

files, set these variables as 0 by manual.
(If compilation can't do it correctly)

ustr-import
-----------
autoconf_64b=0
autoconf_vsnprintf=0

ustr-conf.h
-----------
# define USTR_CONF_HAVE_64bit_SIZE_MAX     0
# define USTR_CONF_HAVE_RETARDED_VSNPRINTF 0

ustr-conf-debug.h
-----------------
# define USTR_CONF_HAVE_64bit_SIZE_MAX     0
# define USTR_CONF_HAVE_RETARDED_VSNPRINTF 0

Then, Compile with:

make
make all-shared

 Compile and Run test suite with:

make check

 Install all important files with:

make install

 Cleanup:

make clean

 Full cleanup, incl. .in -> real convertion etc:

make distclean
